You are a Senior Staff Engineer, Product Designer, Security Engineer, Accessibility Specialist, and Sustainability Expert.

Build a production-ready Next.js 16 application called "CarbonWise AI".

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MISSION
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Design a solution that helps individuals understand, track, and actively reduce their
carbon footprint through AI-powered personalized insights, gamified habit formation,
and real-time lifestyle impact simulation.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PRIMARY GOALS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

* Calculate carbon footprint across 5 lifestyle categories
* Identify major personal emission sources
* Generate personalized AI reduction recommendations
* Simulate impact of lifestyle changes before committing
* Track progress and goals over time
* Motivate behavioral change through gamification

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
TECH STACK (ACTUAL BUILD)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

* Next.js 16.2.9 — App Router, Turbopack
* React 19.2.4
* TypeScript 5.x (strict mode)
* Tailwind CSS v4 — glassmorphism, radial dark, micro-animations
* Firebase Authentication (Email/Password via Firebase SDK)
* Firebase Firestore (primary database — NoSQL collections)
* Prisma + SQLite (fallback database — auto-selected via db-service.ts)
* Google Gemini AI (@google/generative-ai) — coach, autocomplete, challenges
* jose — HttpOnly JWT signing + Firebase JWKS token verification
* Recharts v3 — SSR-safe dynamic charts
* Framer Motion — animated page transitions
* Canvas Confetti — goal completion rewards
* React Hook Form + Zod — form handling and validation
* Lucide React — icon library
* Vitest — unit testing

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ARCHITECTURE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

* Feature-based architecture (features/auth, features/dashboard)
* Dual-mode database abstraction in src/services/db-service.ts
  - Firestore when NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_* keys are present
  - Prisma/SQLite fallback otherwise — zero code changes needed
* Server-side JWT session cookies (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax)
* Firebase onAuthStateChanged listener in AuthContext
* Firebase ID tokens verified server-side via Google JWKS (no service account key)
* All API routes protected via verifyToken() before data access
* Clean separation: UI → API routes → db-service → Firestore/Prisma

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
APPLICATION PAGES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. / — Landing page with interactive commute micro-calculator
2. /auth — Login and sign-up (single page, mode param)
3. /assessment — 5-step carbon wizard with AI natural language autocomplete
4. /dashboard — Recharts analytics, score card, goals list, achievements
5. /coach — Gemini AI sustainability coach with message history
6. /goals — Action planner with AI-generated recommendations
7. /simulator — Lifestyle slider simulator with AI suggest plan button
8. /challenges — Weekly AI-generated eco-challenges board
9. /profile — User level, XP, badges, assessment reset

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
API ENDPOINTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Auth:
  POST /api/auth/login         — verify Firebase ID token, issue session cookie
  POST /api/auth/signup        — register user in db-service, issue session cookie
  POST /api/auth/logout        — clear session cookie
  GET  /api/auth/session       — verify session cookie, return user profile

Carbon:
  GET/POST/DELETE /api/carbon/assessment   — CRUD for carbon assessment records
  POST /api/carbon/parse-assessment        — Gemini parses natural language → assessment fields

Dashboard:
  GET /api/dashboard           — aggregated user stats (assessment, goals, challenges, achievements)

Goals:
  GET/POST/PATCH /api/goals    — CRUD for user goals + XP/level update on completion
  GET /api/goals/recommend     — Gemini-generated personalized goal recommendations

Challenges:
  GET/POST/PATCH /api/challenges — user challenge enrollment and completion

Coach:
  POST /api/chat               — Gemini streaming chat with carbon context
  GET  /api/coach/report       — Gemini full assessment report generation

Simulator:
  GET /api/simulator/recommend — Gemini-suggested optimal simulator configuration

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
AI FEATURES (Gemini Integration)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. AI Assessment Autocomplete
   - User types natural language description of their lifestyle
   - Gemini parses it into structured 5-field assessment values
   - Falls back to sliders if Gemini is unavailable

2. Dynamic AI Weekly Challenges
   - Gemini generates 3 custom challenges based on user's top emission category
   - Appended to static challenge catalog with "AI Recommended" badge

3. Action Planner Goal Recommendations
   - Gemini produces personalized goal list ranked by CO₂ reduction and difficulty
   - Uses user's actual assessment percentages as context

4. Simulator AI Suggest Plan
   - Gemini returns optimal slider values for maximum score improvement
   - User can apply them with one click

5. AI Sustainability Coach Chat
   - Full Gemini conversation with assessment context injected as system prompt
   - Local heuristic fallback when no API key is configured

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Implemented:
* Firebase Authentication — industry-standard identity provider
* JWKS verification — Firebase tokens verified against Google's public certs
* HttpOnly session cookies — prevents XSS token theft
* SameSite=Lax cookies — mitigates CSRF
* Zod input validation on all API routes
* Parameterized queries (Prisma) — prevents SQL injection
* bcryptjs password hashing (10 rounds) — fallback mode
* No secrets in NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables
* Auth loading guard — prevents flash of unauthenticated UI (see navigation.tsx, page.tsx)

Recommended for production:
* Tighten Firestore Security Rules to user-scoped access
* Rate limiting on /api/auth/login and /api/auth/signup
* CSP headers in next.config.ts
* NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL set for correct OG image resolution

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ACCESSIBILITY REQUIREMENTS (WCAG 2.1 AA)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

* Semantic HTML5 landmarks
* Keyboard navigation throughout
* Visible focus rings (focus:ring-2 focus:ring-brand)
* Explicit label associations on all form controls
* High color contrast (white/brand-green on dark backgrounds)
* ARIA labels on icon-only buttons
* Reduced motion adherence

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
DESIGN SYSTEM
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

* Dark theme — base color #090d10
* Brand green — #10b981 (emerald-500)
* Glassmorphism cards — GlassCard component
* Radial glow backdrops behind hero sections
* Micro-animations — pulse-glow, slide-in toasts, spin loaders
* Loading states — animate-pulse skeleton placeholders during auth resolve
* Typography — Geist Sans (primary) + Geist Mono (code)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
KEY IMPLEMENTATION NOTES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

* All client pages use "use client" — metadata must use document.title in useEffect
* Export `viewport` separately from `metadata` in layout.tsx (Next.js 16 requirement)
* Recharts must be dynamically imported with ssr:false to avoid hydration errors
* Canvas Confetti must be dynamically imported (no SSR support)
* Auth loading guard: render skeleton placeholders while `loading === true` to prevent
  flash of logged-out UI in navigation and hero CTA
* db-service.ts is the single source of truth for all database operations —
  never call prisma directly from API routes
* Firebase ID token is obtained client-side via firebaseUser.getIdToken(),
  sent to /api/auth/login, verified server-side, then a session JWT cookie is issued

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
DATABASE MODELS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Firestore collections (primary):
  users             — id, name, email, points, level, createdAt
  assessments       — userId, transport*, energy*, food*, shopping*, waste*, scores, createdAt
  goals             — userId, title, category, co2Reduction, difficulty, status, createdAt
  userChallenges    — userId, challengeCode, status, joinedAt, completedAt
  achievements      — userId, title, description, icon, unlockedAt

Prisma models (fallback SQLite — schema.prisma):
  User, CarbonAssessment, Goal, UserChallenge, Achievement

